## 1.1 Prior knowledge covariate

Prior knowledge is included as a covariate in the models below. I sum the pre-study correlation-definition score and slope-definition score into one composite prior-knowledge score. This keeps the covariate simple and interpretable. The composite ranges from 0 to 2.

```{r prior-knowledge-summary}
if (exists("prior_participant") && nrow(prior_participant) > 0) {
  prior_summary <- prior_participant |>
    group_by(group) |>
    summarise(
      n_participants = sum(!is.na(prior_total)),
      mean_prior_correlation = mean(prior_correlation_score, na.rm = TRUE),
      mean_prior_slope = mean(prior_slope_score, na.rm = TRUE),
      mean_prior_total = mean(prior_total, na.rm = TRUE),
      sd_prior_total = sd(prior_total, na.rm = TRUE),
      .groups = "drop"
    ) |>
    arrange(group)

  prior_summary |> pretty_table()
} else {
  cat('<div class="note-box"><strong>Prior knowledge file not found.</strong> Models below are not adjusted for prior knowledge.</div>')
}
```

