  text_lecture_p <- text_lm_table |> filter(term == "lecture_typePlotWise") |> pull(p_value)
  text_practice_p <- text_lm_table |> filter(term == "practice_typePlotWise") |> pull(p_value)
  text_interaction_p <- text_lm_table |> filter(term == "lecture_typePlotWise:practice_typePlotWise") |> pull(p_value)
  text_prior_est <- text_lm_table |> filter(term == "prior_total") |> pull(estimate)
  text_prior_p <- text_lm_table |> filter(term == "prior_total") |> pull(p_value)

  cat(
    '<div class="note-box"><strong>Interpretation: open-ended conceptual reasoning.</strong><br><br>',
    'The open-ended text-response score is the primary conceptual outcome in this report. This score is lowest in <strong>',
    as.character(lowest_text$group), '</strong> (M = ', round(lowest_text$mean_conceptual_question_score, 3),
    ' out of 4) and highest in <strong>', as.character(best_text$group), '</strong> (M = ',
    round(best_text$mean_conceptual_question_score, 3), ' out of 4). The two conditions that saw the PlotWise lecture, ',
    '<strong>PC</strong> and <strong>PP</strong>, are descriptively higher than the two control-lecture conditions. ',
    'After controlling for prior knowledge, the model shows a positive PlotWise lecture term (estimate = ', round(text_lecture_est, 3),
    ', p = ', text_lecture_p, '), while the practice term is weaker (p = ', text_practice_p,
    ') and the interaction is not clear (p = ', text_interaction_p, '). ',
    'The prior-knowledge covariate is also included in this model (estimate = ', round(text_prior_est, 3), ', p = ', text_prior_p, '). ',
    'I would read this cautiously as evidence that seeing PlotWise modeled in the lecture may have helped participants articulate conceptual relationships between slope and correlation. Prior knowledge is also strongly related to this outcome, so the lecture effect should be interpreted as the remaining condition signal after accounting for baseline definitions.',
    '</div>'
  )
